  "market_context": "XAUUSD price reaches into a fair value gap zone around 4490–4510 on the daily chart. Monday had expanded away bullishly, and price is now pulling back into the discount FVG, requiring a reversal candle to confirm continuation higher.",
  "key_observation": "The initial daily candle 2 closure is mixed — it qualifies as both a bullish and bearish candle 2 closure (OHLC ambiguous), making it a poor reversal candle. Hourly change in state of delivery exists but is not ideal, so intraday confirmation fails and price takes out the low.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify price reaching into the daily fair value gap around 4490–4510 after Monday's bullish expansion.",
    "Evaluate the daily candle 2 closure and note it is ambiguous — both a bullish and bearish candle 2 closure, not an ideal reversal candle.",
    "Drop to the 1H timeframe to look for intraday change in state of delivery confirmation of the bullish reversal.",
    "Observe that the hourly CISD is marked but is mixed (bullish and bearish model), so additional intraday confirmation is required.",
    "Wait for price to open, make a low, and form a new continuation higher — but price fails to respect the area and takes out the low.",
    "Wait for a new daily closure; Thursday prints a proper bullish reversal candle (open-low-high-close) which is a much cleaner candle 2 closure than the prior attempt.",
    "Identify the protected swing and invalidation level below Thursday's low.",
    "Anticipate Friday to form a candle 3 continuation, closing strongly above and creating a new protected swing on the daily.",
    "Project a candle 4 continuation on Monday reaching for the prior daily highs."
  ],
  "outcome": "Thursday formed the proper bullish reversal candle, Friday closed over as candle 3 continuation, setting up Monday candle 4 expansion into the highs.",
  "lessons": "A mixed (OHLC ambiguous) candle 2 closure is not a valid reversal signal even if a hourly CISD appears. Wait for a clean reversal candle (open-low-high-close for bullish) and a protected swing before anticipating continuation; failed setups often require another daily candle to form proper structure.",
